            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "As I understand it, it's an [elaborated type specifier](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/elaborated_type_specifier) that we've added deliberately. Most of the time it really doesn't matter (as you say) but occasionally there are useful.\r\n\r\n~I think we can drop the macro in the master branch (because the macro was specifically to support a really old version of MSVC) but we do want to keep the `enum`.~ That last sentence isn't true...",
