            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> But can you explain why you need it? It seems that it's only useful when type name is somehow hidden.\r\n\r\nMost of the time we don't need it. I think it is only for when the type name is hidden, as you say. I doubt that it that happens often, but it probably happen occasionally.\r\n\r\n> class/struct/union is not generated for other cases so it's not clear why it's needed specifically for enums.\r\n\r\nIt is for struct and union at least. Although that's mostly for C compatibility because\r\n\r\n```\r\nstruct S1 {};\r\n```\r\n\r\ncan only be used as `struct S1` while\r\n\r\n```\r\ntypedef struct {} S2;\r\n```\r\n\r\ncan be used as `S2`.\r\n\r\n-----------------------------------\r\n\r\nYou can work around this by telling Cython that\r\n\r\n```\r\ncdef extern from \"file.hpp\":\r\n    # ...\r\n    ctypedef enum_private enum_public\r\n```\r\n\r\nand then it'll just write the typedef name.",
